11:43.750 --> 11:44.791
Normally,

11:44.791 --> 11:46.458
it will take 2 or 3 sleep cycles

11:46.541 --> 11:49.000
to re-activate your memories,

11:49.291 --> 11:50.750
that is, to restore them.

11:51.333 --> 11:53.083
But I must warn you.

11:53.083 --> 11:55.291
Using this method to restore your memories,

11:55.500 --> 11:57.000
once 72 hours have passed,

11:57.250 --> 11:58.958
those memories will be permanent.

11:59.500 --> 12:00.000
Do you mean to say,

12:00.000 --> 12:01.583
Do you mean to say,

12:01.875 --> 12:04.333
if I want to remove these memories again,

12:05.041 --> 12:06.625
I'd need another operation

12:06.750 --> 12:07.833
within 72 hours?

12:08.083 --> 12:08.750
To be specific,

12:08.791 --> 12:12.416
the 72 hours begins once your memory starts to restore itself.

12:12.708 --> 12:14.000
Also, the next operation wouldn't be an extraction,

12:14.166 --> 12:15.500
it would be a permanent deletion.

12:15.708 --> 12:16.916
With current technology,

12:17.083 --> 12:19.208
it's impossible to store the memories a second time.

12:20.083 --> 12:21.166
During this time,

12:21.208 --> 12:23.125
Mr. Jiang, you can think everything through.

12:23.208 --> 12:25.458
